This paper proposes a language model that combines symbolic knowledge from a knowledge graph with an RNN language model. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The model also involves training on a new dataset, which could potentially fall under the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The use of a knowledge graph suggests that the paper may also be relevant to Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Database (cs.DB) sub-categories.
